Date: Mon, 31 Mar 1997 14:01:40 -0500
Via: Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy <BSE-L@RZ.UNI-KARLSRUHE.DE>
From: Mary Fishler-Fisk <Nupensmith@aol.com>
Subject: Re: CJD, blood donors and bovine blood product
If I am not reading their recommendations incorrectly, WHO recommended
excluding members of families of "inherited" CJD victims, not members of all
families of CJD sufferers.
If, in fact, they do limit it to families of "inherited" CJD victims, how do
they propose identifying those families with the inherited CJD vs. sporadic
or iatrophic? In the US there seems to be no tracking of CJD at all, much
less identifying the genetic strains of CJD.
Second, if CJD is "inherited," how would the blood from family members be
infectious? Is WHO making a backhanded statement that "inherited" CJD is
infectious?
---
Mary Fishler-Fisk
